Well it's been a while since i have updated. in about 4 weeks i am going to miss the one thing i loved to do. I hated it but i proved to so many people with in those 4 years that i would never give up. and now as i finsh watching firday night lights and start to miss football so much. going to the wieght lifting room to get equipment. getting up at 7 a.m. the next morning to the locker room and smelling the awful smell. find my same lock that i had for 3 years. place all my stuff in it. putting on my helmet and it hurting my head. untill the last 20 mins of practice where you know where your going and everyone pushs each other. having the one person you race up and down keep pushing it other. then people polling how many weeks until i died on the hill. which i never did but i think i should have gotten the money. taking my inhealer every 10 mins. kevin going you alright. then going back to the locker room to come back an hour later. also do this all over again. for the next three days. getting hosed down like a bunch of cattle. then doing hitting drills going with smith or crushing alex. lol. you figure u wouldn't miss something u  didn't play in that much, but i have memeories of the few times that i did. or the interception i got before a game that we filmed. (never got that tape) lol. or aponta coming over to e going malave even u can tackle this guys. idk. when i was in there i did things or made the tackle. idk. if coach was afraid of me with my asthma or what. see unlike derek i got respect from everyone becuase when u went against me it was had to do what u wanted. doing the shoots and i would be infront of someone and then trying to get someone else to get in front of them. every friday wearing my jersey to school. friday nights under that lights. you can never get a rush like this and i will never get that again. anyone who on the team knows i tried and i was good not great but good. i wish i went to all the senoir suppers becuase i knew thhey always had fun. but no matt had to work. idk what's with this post. i have been thinking about this for a while. i wish had one more shot at this. being broken mentillal and phyiscaly excuasted. also missing the peep rally right before the high game while the whole school is in the game and we tlak about that we are going to win and the whole school cheers u on the starting line for offense and defense then the rest of the senoirs. well........ yea since i got this off finally i feel alittle less depressed about somethings. oo yea someone i think wants to shoot me so yea........ things just get better.

(ps ny lotto sucks) i don't know why people have such a hard time getting around the first time they go we figured it out in like 2 sec. it took about 30 mins on the subway which only cost 2 bucks to ride and if u really want u can get rise it all day lol. we get to the gate we have to go in and for some reason our tickets weren't working ooo was i getting pissed. but then they did so we went. our seats weren't that bad were on the upper middle behide first base. we just had alittle trouble seeing complete down the right field line. omg the guys behide us were so cool. even thou sean was wearing his boston hat they were kidding around with us the whole game. i have come to relize it is no the yankee fans that start shit. it is the red sox fans. (even acouple red soxs fan admittied to it)Some dude had a sign that that said juice up giambi and start waving it in a yankees face so of course the yankee grabed the sign tore it up and then the red sox fan tried to punch the yankee fan and missed then i like a flash there were cops. no one was watching the game as all the people were turning around tino jacks a home run to tie it in the 4th. i much as a hate jeter he didn't deserve to get hit in the face. i think payback will happen on monday for that. yes i know the final score was 7-3 or 7-2. but i idc. it was the most amazing thing in the world to go to a yankee red sox game and just watch it in person. if u care to know more call my cell i will tell u about my day it was great. sry to all my friends that i have ingored or not talken to becuase i worked to much.

You Are 20 Years Old
20
Under 12: You are a kid at heart. You still have an optimistic life view - and you look at the world with awe. 13-19: You are a teenager at heart. You question authority and are still trying to find your place in this world. 20-29: You are a twentysomething at heart. You feel excited about what's to come... love, work, and new experiences. 30-39: You are a thirtysomething at heart. You've had a taste of success and true love, but you want more! 40+: You are a mature adult. You've been through most of the ups and downs of life already. Now you get to sit back and relax.
